  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Right now a single archive can grow infinitely in size (in theory). The date range alone will not guarantee that it won't contain messages that will exceed any feasible amount of data.\r\n\r\nThis can be problematic when message data is extract to reconstruct the protobuf archives and the amount of data to be loaded exceeds the available memory.\r\n\r\nWe should define some max cap on the size of a single archive and adjust the archive protocol to take it into account.",
